-- 1. Heliocare 360 Airgel SPF50+
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is Heliocare 360 Airgel right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Oily or combination skin</strong> — The foam-to-serum texture absorbs instantly with zero residue, so your skin stays matte and comfortable all day.</li>
<li><strong>You dislike the feel of traditional sunscreens</strong> — The airgel format is unlike any SPF you have tried — it melts in and disappears completely.</li>
<li><strong>Post-treatment patients who need daily SPF</strong> — Lightweight enough to layer over serums after Botox, fillers or Dermapen without disturbing the skin.</li>
<li><strong>Patients who skip SPF because of texture</strong> — This is Dr. Bangalee's most recommended SPF for patients who admit they cannot stand the feel of sunscreen.</li>
<li><strong>All skin tones in the South African climate</strong> — Leaves no white cast and no greasiness, even in high heat and humidity.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare 360 Airgel works — the science</h3>
<p><strong>Fernblock®</strong>, a clinically validated extract of Polypodium leucotomos fern, forms the biological backbone of this formula — absorbing UV radiation at the cellular level and reducing DNA damage before it accumulates. The <strong>360° filter system</strong> combines UVA, UVB, infrared and visible/blue light protection in a single application, addressing every wavelength that drives photoageing and pigmentation. The <strong>airgel delivery system</strong> encapsulates these actives in micro-foam droplets that burst on contact with skin, releasing a weightless protective film that bonds to the surface without blocking pores or leaving residue.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> The foam bursts on contact and absorbs within seconds — skin feels fresh, not heavy. No white cast, no shine.<br><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> You will stop noticing you are wearing SPF. Skin feels like itself, not coated. Makeup sits better on top.<br><strong>Month 1+:</strong> Consistent daily use prevents the incremental UV damage that causes fine lines and pigmentation. Combined with Dr. Bangalee's treatments, results last longer.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 Airgel</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply as the final step of your morning skincare routine, after moisturiser or serum.</li>
<li>Dispense a generous amount (a full finger's width) and apply evenly to face, neck and décolletage.</li>
<li>Allow 30 seconds to absorb before applying makeup or going outdoors.</li>
<li>Reapply every 2 hours during prolonged sun exposure or after swimming and sweating.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Fernblock®</td><td>Polypodium leucotomos fern extract — absorbs UV at a cellular level, reduces DNA damage and enhances the effectiveness of topical SPF filters.</td></tr>
<tr><td>UVA/UVB Chemical Filters</td><td>Broad-spectrum photostable filters block both burning UVB rays and the deeper, ageing UVA rays that penetrate glass and cloud cover.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infrared Protection</td><td>Neutralises infrared radiation — the heat energy that penetrates deeper than UV and drives collagen breakdown and pigmentation.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Blue Light Filters</td><td>Shields skin from high-energy visible light emitted by screens and LED lighting — increasingly linked to pigmentation in darker skin tones.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antioxidant Complex</td><td>Scavenges free radicals generated by UV exposure, preventing the oxidative stress that accelerates photoageing.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>"The Airgel is my answer to every patient who tells me they hate wearing sunscreen. The texture genuinely removes every objection — there is nothing to feel, nothing to see, and no reason not to wear it every day. In our climate, I consider daily SPF non-negotiable for anyone receiving aesthetic treatments, and the Airgel makes compliance effortless." — Dr. Rajeev Bangalee, MB BS</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>What our patients say</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<td>"I have tried every sunscreen on the market and always stopped using them within a week. The Airgel is the first one I actually look forward to putting on — it feels like nothing." — Priya, 34</td>
<td>"Dr. Bangalee recommended this after my Botox and I was amazed at how light it is. No white cast, no stickiness. I wear it every day now." — Tracey, 42</td>
<td>"Living in Durban, I need SPF but I hate feeling sweaty. This foam absorbs in seconds and my skin stays matte all day even in the heat." — Candice, 29</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Can I wear this under makeup?</strong></td><td>Yes — the airgel formula is specifically designed to layer under foundation and powder without pilling or causing makeup to slide. Allow 30 seconds to absorb before applying makeup.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Is it suitable for sensitive or post-treatment skin?</strong></td><td>The Airgel contains both chemical and mineral filters. For very reactive or post-procedure skin, Dr. Bangalee recommends the Mineral Tolerance Fluid instead, which is 100% mineral.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Does it leave a white cast?</strong></td><td>No. The foam format contains no zinc oxide in visible quantities, so it is completely transparent on all skin tones including darker complexions.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>How much do I use per application?</strong></td><td>Use a generous amount — approximately a full finger's width across the face. Under-applying SPF significantly reduces its protection level.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>What is Fernblock®?</strong></td><td>Polypodium leucotomos extract — a fern plant antioxidant that absorbs UV radiation at the cellular level, reducing DNA damage and photoageing. Clinically proven to enhance the effectiveness of topical SPF.</td></tr>
</table>
