-- 2. Heliocare 360 Fluid Cream SPF50+
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is Heliocare 360 Fluid Cream right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Normal to dry skin</strong> — Combines broad-spectrum 360° sun protection with active hydration so you can replace your morning moisturiser and SPF in a single step.</li>
<li><strong>Patients who experience dryness after aesthetic treatments</strong> — The ceramide-supporting formula restores comfort to skin that feels tight or sensitised post-procedure.</li>
<li><strong>Women who want to simplify their morning routine</strong> — SPF, moisturiser and antioxidant protection in one product, reducing steps without compromising results.</li>
<li><strong>Anti-ageing patients on a daily maintenance routine</strong> — Provides the UV protection that maintains Botox and filler results for longer, while the hydrating actives support skin quality.</li>
<li><strong>Patients spending extended time outdoors</strong> — The cream base provides a comfortable, durable protective layer that stays effective in South African heat.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare 360 Fluid Cream works — the science</h3>
<p>The <strong>Fernblock® complex</strong> neutralises UV-induced DNA damage at a cellular level, working alongside the <strong>360° filter system</strong> to block UVA, UVB, infrared radiation and blue light simultaneously. The fluid cream base is formulated with <strong>glycerin and humectant actives</strong> that draw moisture into the skin and create a sustained hydration reservoir throughout the day. Unlike traditional sunscreens that sit on the skin surface, the cream vehicle integrates with the skin barrier, delivering protection and hydration in one bound layer rather than two competing products.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Skin feels hydrated and comfortable from the first application — a clean, non-greasy finish that dry skin responds to immediately.<br><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Morning tightness and dryness reduces. Skin starts the day already balanced rather than needing to recover from the night.<br><strong>Month 1+:</strong> Consistent UV protection prevents the cumulative sun damage that deepens fine lines and creates pigmentation. Skin looks and behaves younger with fewer interruptions to hydration.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 Fluid Cream</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply as the last step of your morning skincare routine, after serum and any targeted treatments.</li>
<li>Warm a generous amount between fingertips and press into skin from the centre outward, covering face, neck and décolletage.</li>
<li>Allow 1–2 minutes to fully absorb before applying makeup if desired.</li>
<li>Reapply every 2 hours during prolonged outdoor exposure.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Fernblock®</td><td>Fern-derived antioxidant that provides internal cellular UV defence — amplifying the protection delivered by topical filters.</td></tr>
<tr><td>UVA/UVB Broad-Spectrum Filters</td><td>Photostable chemical filters provide reliable, even protection against the full UV spectrum from dawn to dusk.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infrared &amp; Blue Light Protection</td><td>Addresses the wavelengths beyond UV that drive collagen breakdown and post-inflammatory pigmentation.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Glycerin &amp; Hydrating Complex</td><td>Draws moisture into the epidermis and supports the skin barrier, reducing trans-epidermal water loss throughout the day.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antioxidant Blend</td><td>Neutralises free radicals generated by environmental exposure, preventing the oxidative cascade that accelerates skin ageing.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>"The Fluid Cream is what I recommend for patients whose skin tends toward dryness, especially those going through hormonal changes or on certain medications that reduce skin hydration. It gives them everything they need in one morning step — protection, hydration and antioxidant support — and the compliance is excellent because it actually feels nice to use." — Dr. Rajeev Bangalee, MB BS</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>What our patients say</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<td>"My skin was always dry and flaky in the mornings. Since using the Fluid Cream I wake up and my skin already feels comfortable. It has become the one product I cannot go without." — Nadia, 47</td>
<td>"I love that I can use this instead of a separate moisturiser and SPF. One less step and my skin actually looks better for it." — Sandra, 39</td>
<td>"Dr. Bangalee put me on this after my skin peels and the difference in how hydrated my skin feels is remarkable. The SPF protection gives me peace of mind too." — Lerato, 44</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Can this replace my moisturiser entirely?</strong></td><td>For normal to dry skin, yes — the Fluid Cream provides sufficient hydration for most patients as a combined SPF and moisturiser. Very dry skin types may still want to apply a hydrating serum underneath.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Is it suitable for post-treatment use?</strong></td><td>The Fluid Cream contains chemical SPF filters which are generally well-tolerated. However, for very reactive or freshly treated skin, the Mineral Tolerance Fluid (100% mineral) is Dr. Bangalee's first choice.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Does it leave a white cast?</strong></td><td>No — the fluid cream formula is fully transparent and absorbs cleanly on all skin tones.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Can I use it as a makeup base?</strong></td><td>Yes. Allow 1–2 minutes to absorb, then apply foundation as normal. The smooth hydrated base actually improves makeup application and longevity.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>What is Fernblock®?</strong></td><td>Polypodium leucotomos extract — a fern plant antioxidant that absorbs UV radiation at the cellular level, reducing DNA damage and photoageing. Clinically proven to enhance the effectiveness of topical SPF.</td></tr>
