-- 4. Heliocare 360 Oral Capsules 30
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is Heliocare 360 Oral Capsules right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Patients undergoing pigmentation treatment</strong> — Internal photoprotection reinforces your topical SPF to reduce the UV triggers that drive melasma and hyperpigmentation recurrence.</li>
<li><strong>Post-procedure patients</strong> — After Dermapen, skin peels or laser treatments, skin is especially vulnerable to UV damage. Oral capsules add a second line of defence during the healing window.</li>
<li><strong>High sun-exposure lifestyles</strong> — Patients who spend extended time outdoors — sport, farming, outdoor work — get meaningful additional protection that topical SPF alone cannot sustain.</li>
<li><strong>Patients with a family history of skin cancer</strong> — Provides daily systemic antioxidant and photoprotective support as part of a comprehensive prevention strategy.</li>
<li><strong>Those who want to maximise their SPF investment</strong> — Clinical studies show Fernblock® oral supplementation significantly enhances the efficacy of topical sunscreen applied at the same time.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare 360 Oral Capsules work — the science</h3>
<p><strong>Fernblock®</strong>, the concentrated oral form of Polypodium leucotomos extract, is absorbed systemically and distributed to the skin via the bloodstream — providing cellular UV protection from the inside that no topical SPF can replicate. Each capsule delivers <strong>240mg of standardised Fernblock®</strong> alongside a targeted <strong>antioxidant complex including Vitamins C and E, beta-carotene and lycopene</strong>, which collectively neutralise the free radical cascade triggered by UV, infrared and blue light exposure. This dual-action approach — topical filter on the surface, biological protection at the cellular level — is clinically proven to reduce UV-induced immunosuppression, DNA strand breaks and lipid peroxidation more effectively than topical SPF alone.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> No visible or tactile sensation — the capsules work silently at the cellular level.<br><strong>Week 2–4:</strong> Patients managing pigmentation or post-treatment skin often report less reactivity to incidental sun exposure — less redness, less breakthrough darkening.<br><strong>Month 2+:</strong> Consistent oral photoprotection reduces cumulative UV damage. Patients on combined oral + topical SPF show measurably better maintenance of aesthetic treatment results over time.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 Oral Capsules</h3>
<ol>
<li>Take one capsule daily with a meal, 30 minutes before sun exposure where possible.</li>
<li>Continue topical SPF — oral capsules enhance but do not replace topical sunscreen.</li>
<li>During periods of intense sun exposure (beach holidays, outdoor events), a second capsule can be taken at midday.</li>
<li>Use continuously for best results — the cumulative photoprotective and antioxidant benefits increase with consistent daily use.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Fernblock® (Polypodium leucotomos, 240mg)</td><td>Systemic UV defence distributed via bloodstream — reduces DNA photodamage, UV-induced immunosuppression and melanin overproduction at a cellular level.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Vitamin C (ascorbic acid)</td><td>Potent antioxidant that neutralises UV-generated free radicals and supports collagen synthesis — works synergistically with Fernblock® to prevent photoageing.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Vitamin E (tocopherol)</td><td>Fat-soluble antioxidant that protects cell membranes from lipid peroxidation caused by UV and infrared radiation.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Beta-carotene &amp; Lycopene</td><td>Carotenoid antioxidants that accumulate in skin tissue and provide additional free radical scavenging where UV damage occurs.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Zinc</td><td>Supports the immune-modulating and antioxidant enzyme systems that protect skin from UV-induced oxidative stress.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>"The Heliocare Oral capsules are the only internal sun protection supplement I recommend to my patients. The evidence behind Fernblock® is genuinely compelling — it is not a wellness trend, it is a clinically validated photoprotective agent. For my pigmentation patients especially, adding oral protection has made a measurable difference to how long their treatment results last. I take them myself." — Dr. Rajeev Bangalee, MB BS</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>What our patients say</h3>
<table>
<tr>
<td>"I had been struggling with melasma returning every summer despite wearing SPF. Since adding the oral capsules, I have had my first summer without a flare-up in years." — Melissa, 43</td>
<td>"Dr. Bangalee recommended these after my Dermapen course and my skin was noticeably less reactive to sun exposure during recovery. Genuinely surprised at the difference." — Zanele, 37</td>
<td>"I play golf four times a week and these give me peace of mind that I am protected even when I forget to reapply. I will not travel without them." — Gary, 52</td>
</tr>
</table>

<h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Do these replace my topical SPF?</strong></td><td>No — oral capsules are designed to enhance and extend the protection of topical sunscreen, not replace it. Dr. Bangalee always prescribes them alongside a topical Heliocare SPF, never as a standalone.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>How long before I need to take them before sun exposure?</strong></td><td>For best results, take one capsule 30–60 minutes before going outdoors. However, with daily use the cumulative Fernblock® levels in your skin remain elevated throughout the day.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Are they safe to take long-term?</strong></td><td>Yes — Fernblock® has an extensive safety record with over 20 years of clinical use. The formula is free from harmful levels of any ingredient and is well-tolerated for continuous daily use.</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Can I take two capsules on high-exposure days?</strong></td><td>Yes — on beach days, outdoor events or during a holiday in a high-UV destination, a second capsule at midday is recommended and safe.</td></tr>
