-- 5. Heliocare 360 Paediatric Lotion SPF50+ (50ml)
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is Heliocare 360 Paediatric Lotion right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Children from 6 months of age</strong> — Formulated specifically for delicate, developing skin that requires pure mineral protection without chemical SPF irritation.</li>
<li><strong>Parents who want the same trusted SPF brand as their doctor</strong> — Dr. Bangalee uses Heliocare for his patients; the Paediatric Lotion brings the same clinical standard to your family.</li>
<li><strong>Babies with eczema or sensitive skin</strong> — 100% mineral formula with no chemical filters, fragrance or parabens makes this the safest choice for reactive infant skin.</li>
<li><strong>Families spending time outdoors in the South African sun</strong> — 360° protection covering UVA, UVB, infrared and blue light gives children comprehensive coverage during peak sun hours.</li>
<li><strong>Parents who want a product safe for the whole family</strong> — Adults with very sensitive skin can use this too.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare 360 Paediatric Lotion works — the science</h3>
<p>Unlike chemical sunscreens that absorb UV radiation and convert it to heat, the <strong>100% mineral filter system</strong> in this formula physically reflects and scatters UV light before it reaches the skin surface — making it inherently gentler and safer for immature skin barriers. The formula uses <strong>micronised zinc oxide and titanium dioxide</strong> to deliver broad-spectrum UVA and UVB protection, alongside <strong>Fernblock®</strong> for additional cellular-level photoprotection. The entire formula has been dermatologically tested for infant skin, with every ingredient selected for its safety profile and zero sensitising potential.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Absorbs smoothly with minimal white cast for a mineral formula. Skin feels protected without the greasy residue of older mineral sunscreens.<br><strong>Daily use:</strong> Children's skin stays protected during outdoor play, school activities and beach trips without the irritation of harsh chemical SPF products.<br><strong>Long-term:</strong> Consistent childhood sun protection is one of the most impactful steps in lifetime skin cancer prevention — habits formed now matter for decades.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 Paediatric Lotion</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply generously to all exposed skin 15–20 minutes before going outdoors — mineral filters need a few minutes to settle before full protection is active.</li>
<li>Pay special attention to ears, back of neck, tops of feet and shoulders — areas children typically miss.</li>
<li>Reapply every 90–120 minutes during active outdoor play and immediately after swimming or towelling dry.</li>
<li>Do not use on infants under 6 months without medical advice — keep babies in the shade and use protective clothing instead.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Zinc Oxide (mineral)</td><td>Broad-spectrum mineral filter that reflects both UVA and UVB radiation. Safe for infant skin and does not penetrate or irritate the skin barrier.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Titanium Dioxide (mineral)</td><td>UVB-focused mineral filter that works with zinc oxide to provide comprehensive protection with no chemical absorption.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fernblock®</td><td>Provides an additional cellular antioxidant photoprotective layer, further reducing UV-induced DNA damage even in children's developing skin.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fragrance-Free Base</td><td>Completely free of perfumes and fragrance compounds — the leading cause of contact dermatitis and sensitisation in children's skincare products.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Skin-Soothing Emollients</td><td>Gentle moisturising agents maintain the skin barrier and prevent the dryness and irritation that can accompany frequent SPF application in outdoor conditions.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3>
<table>
<tr><td><strong>Dr. Bangalee Recommends</strong></td><td>"As a doctor and a parent, the Paediatric Lotion is what I recommend without hesitation for children. The 100% mineral formula gives me complete confidence in its safety for young skin, and the Fernblock® component provides a level of cellular protection that no other children's SPF I have seen can match. Protecting children's skin now prevents serious consequences decades later." — Dr. Rajeev Bangalee, MB BS</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>What our patients say</h3>
<table>
