-- 6. Heliocare 360 AK Fluid SPF100+
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is Heliocare 360 AK Fluid SPF100+ right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Patients with actinic keratosis</strong> — Medical-grade SPF100+ is the clinical standard of care for patients with pre-cancerous sun lesions, providing the highest available topical UV barrier.</li>
<li><strong>History of skin cancer or melanoma</strong> — If you have been treated for any form of skin cancer, this is the protection level your specialist team recommends for daily life.</li>
<li><strong>Fair-skinned patients with extensive sun damage</strong> — Visible sun spots, deep wrinkling, or a history of many sunburns indicate high UV vulnerability where SPF100+ makes a significant difference.</li>
<li><strong>Immunocompromised patients</strong> — Patients on immunosuppressant medications have reduced ability to repair UV-induced DNA damage — SPF100+ provides the largest margin of protection.</li>
<li><strong>High-altitude or coastal patients with year-round outdoor exposure</strong> — Where UV index regularly exceeds 10, SPF100+ provides meaningful additional protection over standard SPF50.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare 360 AK Fluid SPF100+ works — the science</h3>
<p>SPF100+ is not simply double SPF50 — the mathematics are more significant. <strong>SPF50 blocks 98% of UVB rays; SPF100+ blocks 99%</strong>, meaning half the UVB radiation gets through SPF100+ compared to SPF50 — a clinically meaningful difference for high-risk patients. The formula combines an <strong>ultra-high concentration photostable filter system</strong> with <strong>Fernblock®</strong> to create a dual-barrier: the filters physically and chemically neutralise UV radiation at the surface, while Fernblock® provides cellular-level DNA protection for any radiation that penetrates. <strong>Infrared and blue light protection</strong> complete the 360° shield, addressing the full spectrum of photodamaging wavelengths.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Light fluid texture — the high SPF level does not translate to a heavy or occlusive feel. Absorbs cleanly with a minimal dry-touch finish.<br><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Existing actinic lesions are protected from additional UV aggravation, halting their progression during treatment.<br><strong>Month 1+:</strong> Used consistently as part of a medically supervised protocol, SPF100+ significantly reduces the rate of new lesion formation in high-risk patients.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 AK Fluid SPF100+</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply every morning as the final step of skincare, to face, scalp (if relevant), ears and any other at-risk areas.</li>
<li>Use a generous, even layer — do not under-apply. SPF values are measured at 2mg per cm² — most people apply at 25–50% of the required amount.</li>
<li>Reapply every 2 hours without exception during outdoor exposure. For medical-grade protection, consistent reapplication is as important as the SPF number.</li>
<li>Combine with Heliocare Oral Capsules for maximum systemic photoprotection — Dr. Bangalee prescribes both for the highest-risk patients.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Fernblock®</td><td>Cellular-level UV defence that provides biological protection against the DNA damage SPF filters cannot fully intercept.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ultra-High SPF Filter Complex</td><td>Maximum concentration photostable UVA and UVB filters providing the highest available topical UV blockade — blocks 99% of UVB vs 98% for SPF50.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infrared A Protection</td><td>Addresses the deep-penetrating infrared wavelengths that drive subcutaneous heat damage, collagen breakdown and pigmentation worsening.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Blue Light Filters</td><td>Shields against visible light-induced pigmentation — particularly relevant in post-AK patients where skin reactivity is heightened.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antioxidant Matrix</td><td>Multi-pathway free radical neutralisation to address the oxidative cascade from UV, infrared and environmental exposure simultaneously.</td></tr>
</table>

