-- 7. Heliocare 360 Mineral Tolerance Fluid SPF50
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is Heliocare 360 Mineral Tolerance Fluid right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Post-Dermapen or post-peel skin</strong> — Dr. Bangalee's first-choice SPF for patients after any procedure that disrupts the skin barrier — 100% mineral means zero risk of chemical filter irritation on freshly treated skin.</li>
<li><strong>Rosacea and chronically sensitive skin</strong> — Chemical SPF filters are a common rosacea trigger. The mineral-only formula eliminates this risk entirely while delivering full 360° protection.</li>
<li><strong>Patients who react to most sunscreens</strong> — If you have tried multiple SPF products and experienced redness, stinging or breakouts, the Mineral Tolerance Fluid is almost always tolerated.</li>
<li><strong>Perimenopause skin that has become newly reactive</strong> — Hormonal shifts can make previously tolerant skin suddenly reactive. Switching to mineral SPF removes one of the most common chemical sensitisers.</li>
<li><strong>Post-isotretinoin (Roaccutane) patients</strong> — Skin barrier function is compromised during and after Roaccutane. Mineral-only SPF supports recovery without adding irritants.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare 360 Mineral Tolerance Fluid works — the science</h3>
<p>Chemical SPF filters work by absorbing UV radiation and converting it to heat — a process that can trigger flushing, sensitisation and reactive oxygen species in already-compromised skin. The <strong>100% mineral filter system</strong> in this formula operates entirely differently: <strong>micronised zinc oxide and titanium dioxide physically reflect and scatter UV radiation</strong> before it makes contact with the skin surface, with no heat conversion and no biological interaction with the skin barrier. <strong>Fernblock®</strong> provides supplementary cellular photoprotection, and the <strong>calming base</strong> contains soothing actives that actively reduce inflammation rather than simply avoiding it.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Notably gentle on application — no stinging, no flushing, no tightness even on freshly treated skin. Absorbs to a soft, comfortable finish.<br><strong>Week 1–2 post-treatment:</strong> Skin heals without UV-aggravated setbacks. Post-procedure redness resolves faster when protected with a non-irritating mineral SPF.<br><strong>Ongoing:</strong> Rosacea patients typically notice reduced flush frequency and intensity when chemical filters are eliminated from the daily routine.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 Mineral Tolerance Fluid</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply as the final step each morning — immediately after any post-procedure products Dr. Bangalee has prescribed.</li>
<li>Apply generously and evenly to all exposed areas. On sensitive or reactive skin, pat rather than rub to minimise friction during application.</li>
<li>For post-procedure patients: begin using from Day 1 after treatment as directed by Dr. Bangalee's aftercare instructions.</li>
<li>Reapply every 2 hours when outdoors. Avoid peak sun hours (10am–3pm) during the immediate post-procedure recovery window.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Zinc Oxide (mineral)</td><td>Primary broad-spectrum filter that physically reflects UVA and UVB. The most gentle SPF active available — zero sensitising potential and anti-inflammatory properties.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Titanium Dioxide (mineral)</td><td>Enhances UVB protection in combination with zinc oxide. Both minerals are photostable and do not degrade with sun exposure.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fernblock®</td><td>Provides cellular UV defence even for radiation that scatters past the mineral filters — particularly important for post-procedure skin with a compromised barrier.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Calming &amp; Soothing Complex</td><td>Anti-inflammatory actives reduce post-procedure redness and support barrier repair during the healing window after Dermapen, peels or laser.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Fragrance-Free &amp; Paraben-Free Base</td><td>Completely free of the most common sensitising ingredients found in conventional sunscreens — safe for the most reactive skin conditions.</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>Dr. Bangalee's clinical perspective</h3>
<table>
