<h3>How Heliocare 360 Pigment Solution Fluid works — the science</h3>
<p>Standard sunscreens prevent UV-triggered pigmentation by blocking the UV stimulus — but they do nothing for existing spots. The <strong>Pigment Solution Fluid adds a targeted depigmenting complex</strong> to the 360° filter system: <strong>Niacinamide</strong> inhibits the transfer of melanin granules from melanocytes to keratinocytes, preventing discolouration from forming; <strong>Thiamidol</strong> (a next-generation tyrosinase inhibitor) blocks the enzyme that drives melanin overproduction at the source; and <strong>Fernblock®</strong> provides cellular-level UV defence that reduces the UV signal triggering the entire pigmentation cascade. Together, these create a triple-action approach: block UV, inhibit melanin synthesis, and prevent melanin distribution — daily, without any additional effort.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Week 1–2:</strong> Existing spots do not darken with sun exposure as they typically would. New sun-triggered spots stop forming.<br><strong>Month 1–2:</strong> Existing dark spots begin to fade measurably. Skin tone becomes more even across the face with consistent daily use.<br><strong>Month 3+:</strong> Combined with Dr. Bangalee's professional pigmentation treatments, the Pigment Solution Fluid amplifies and prolongs results — maintaining the improvement achieved in-clinic every single day.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 Pigment Solution Fluid</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply as the final morning skincare step to clean skin after serum and any targeted treatments Dr. Bangalee has prescribed.</li>
<li>Apply a generous, even layer to the full face, paying extra attention to areas of active pigmentation or recurring dark spots.</li>
<li>Allow 30–60 seconds to absorb before applying makeup, if desired.</li>
<li>Reapply every 2 hours during sun exposure — do not reduce frequency because this is an active treatment product.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
