</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare 360 Paediatric Lotion 200ml works — the science</h3>
<p>Identical to the standard Paediatric Lotion in formulation, the 200ml size delivers the same clinically validated protection: <strong>100% mineral filters</strong> (zinc oxide and titanium dioxide) that physically reflect UVA and UVB radiation without chemical skin penetration, alongside <strong>Fernblock®</strong> for cellular photoprotection and a <strong>soothing, fragrance-free emollient base</strong> safe from 6 months. The generous format means parents can apply the correct amount — 2mg per cm² of skin surface — without rationing, which is the most common cause of underprotection in children's sunscreen use.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Smooth, gentle application with minimal white cast for a mineral formula. Children tolerate it well — no stinging and no strong scent.<br><strong>Daily use:</strong> Consistent full-body coverage without the anxiety of product running low. The generous format encourages proper application amounts.<br><strong>Long-term:</strong> Children protected from UV during their formative years have dramatically lower lifetime skin cancer risk — the most impactful sun protection decision you can make for them.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare 360 Paediatric Lotion 200ml</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply generously to all exposed skin 20 minutes before outdoor activity — give the mineral filters time to settle and bind to the skin surface.</li>
<li>Do not forget ears, the back of the neck, shoulders, tops of feet and the scalp parting — the areas children most often burn.</li>
<li>Reapply every 90 minutes during active outdoor play and immediately after swimming, towelling or excessive sweating.</li>
<li>For school days, send the bottle for outdoor sports — children should not rely on morning-only application for full-day outdoor activities.</li>
