-- 15. Heliocare Compacts Oil Free SPF50
update public.products set description = $desc$
<h3>Is Heliocare Compacts Oil Free SPF50 right for you?</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Anyone who wears makeup and cannot reapply liquid SPF during the day</strong> — The Compacts solve the single biggest barrier to adequate daily sun protection: how to reapply SPF without destroying your makeup.</li>
<li><strong>Patients using tinted Heliocare SPF (Beige or Bronze)</strong> — The Compacts are specifically designed to reapply over tinted SPF — they add protection without altering the colour match underneath.</li>
<li><strong>Office workers and commuters</strong> — Morning SPF provides peak protection for approximately 2 hours in direct sunlight. For patients with any outdoor commute or lunch break, the Compacts are the only practical midday reapplication option.</li>
<li><strong>Travellers and on-the-go patients</strong> — The compact format fits in any handbag, desk drawer or gym bag — making midday SPF reapplication a 10-second routine wherever you are.</li>
<li><strong>Post-pigmentation treatment patients</strong> — Consistent reapplication throughout the day is critical during active pigmentation treatment. The Compacts make this achievable for the first time.</li>
</ul>

<h3>How Heliocare Compacts Oil Free SPF50 works — the science</h3>
<p>Conventional sunscreen reapplication requires washing off existing makeup, applying liquid SPF, and reapplying full makeup — making it completely impractical for most patients. The <strong>Compacts formula</strong> encapsulates <strong>UVA and UVB SPF50 filters alongside Fernblock®</strong> in a pressed powder matrix that deposits a new protective film directly over existing makeup without disturbing the products underneath. The <strong>oil-free powder base</strong> simultaneously absorbs any midday sebum, refreshes the complexion and adds a subtle natural finish — so reapplying SPF actually improves the appearance of skin rather than compromising it. This removes every practical barrier to adequate sun protection during a normal working day.</p>

<h3>What you will notice — and when</h3>
<p><strong>Immediately:</strong> Apply over makeup in 10 seconds. Skin looks freshened, matte, and fully protected — with no disruption to the makeup or skincare layers underneath.<br><strong>Daily use:</strong> The discipline of midday reapplication becomes effortless. The Compacts go from being an inconvenient obligation to a satisfying midday routine that makes skin look better.<br><strong>Long-term:</strong> Patients who achieve genuine twice-daily reapplication see meaningfully better outcomes from pigmentation and anti-ageing treatments — the accumulated UV that slips through a morning-only SPF routine is eliminated.</p>

<h3>How to use Heliocare Compacts Oil Free SPF50</h3>
<ol>
<li>Apply morning SPF and makeup as normal — the Compacts are your midday reapplication tool, not your morning SPF.</li>
<li>At midday or after 2 hours of sun exposure, sweep the compact generously over the entire face using the included applicator — coverage, not just a light dusting.</li>
<li>Pay attention to nose, forehead, cheekbones and chin — the areas with the highest UV exposure and the most SPF degradation from environmental contact.</li>
<li>Reapply again after any extended outdoor period. The compact can be used multiple times daily — one compact typically provides 2–3 months of midday use.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Key ingredients &amp; what they do</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Ingredient</th><th>What it does for you</th></tr>
<tr><td>Fernblock®</td><td>Cellular UV photoprotection delivered even in powder form — the biological protection layer that standard powder SPFs cannot provide.</td></tr>
<tr><td>UVA/UVB Broad-Spectrum Filters</td><td>Comprehensive photostable filter system in pressed powder form — adds a fresh protective layer directly over existing SPF and makeup.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Oil-Free Powder Base</td><td>Absorbs midday sebum while depositing fresh SPF — the dual function that makes reapplication both practical and cosmetically beneficial.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Natural Pigments</td><td>Neutral tone that provides slight coverage and unification across a range of skin tones without adding visible colour or altering existing makeup.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Antioxidant Support</td><td>Helps neutralise the free radical accumulation that occurs in the SPF layer throughout the day as it absorbs UV radiation.</td></tr>
</table>

